      {
        "id": 3,
        "lineId": 1,
        "beatId": 4,
        "bookId": null,
        "positionWithinLine": 0,
        "positionInBeat": 0,
        "title": "Third 1,000 Words",
        "description": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "--- Add Your Details Above this Line ---"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Third 1,000 Words",
                "bold": true
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "In a longer story, this section would be called the midpoint. Here’s where the Hero stubs their toe. Things looked good – now the Villain heaves a monkey wrench into the works! Trouble-with a capital “Boo!” pops up. Technically this is known as a “plot complication,” which is just a literary way of saying it’s a mess. In short, then, this complication is generally something the Hero did not nor could have possibly expected; it may even be a break the Villain did not count on. But it makes a hell of a situation for the Hero."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Genre Examples: ",
                "bold": true
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "bulleted-list",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Sports: ",
                    "bold": true
                  },
                  {
                    "text": "The Hero is a flashy player, without whom his team cannot win championship vital to the athletic future of the small college. In phase one, the main problem is set forth. In phase two, the path looks easy – Hero going like house afire. Phase three, complication: vital blocking back breaks leg before the crucial game!"
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Science Fiction:",
                    "bold": true
                  },
                  {
                    "text": " The Hero is hastily finishing a spaceship with which to visit Mars; must get special Martian desert weed to stave off dreadful scourge which threatens to destroy Earth. Complication: enemy scientists corner market on beryllium, vitally essential metal for construction of spaceship."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Detective Fiction:",
                    "bold": true
                  },
                  {
                    "text": " The Detective Hero is hunting Red Jornegan, a gangster, whose fingerprints were found all over a gun that murdered a cop. Tracks Jornegan to hide-out. Complication: Finds Jornegan dead, killer’s gun lying across the room with Jornegan’s fingerprints on it! "
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Love Story: ",
                    "bold": true
                  },
                  {
                    "text": "The Hero admires a movie idol, wangles an introduction, succeeds in making him very, very interested. The soft odor of orange blossoms in the distance, and then... complication! Learns his contract has a no wedding clause."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Adventure: ",
                    "bold": true
                  },
                  {
                    "text": "The Hero, a Foreign Legion Lieutenant, is besieged by a mob of howling Bedouins. Must carry news of uprising to post. Remembers cache of ammunition in the desert. Finds it. Complication: Bullets are for a different rifle!"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Breakdown:",
                "bold": true
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "bulleted-list",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Third 1,000 Words ends on page 13 - 15, from the 40-60% mark in the story."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
